{"title":"The New MET Estro Mips Road Helmet is Built for Comfort and Safety","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/18/the-new-met-estro-mips-road-helmet-is-built-for-comfort-and-safety/","date":1634571558000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"688\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110703/met-helmets-estro-mipsMET-Estro-Mips_P5102654_%40ulyssedaessle-e1634571514258-800x688.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110703/met-helmets-estro-mipsMET-Estro-Mips_P5102654_%40ulyssedaessle-e1634571514258-800x688.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110703/met-helmets-estro-mipsMET-Estro-Mips_P5102654_%40ulyssedaessle-e1634571514258-297x255.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110703/met-helmets-estro-mipsMET-Estro-Mips_P5102654_%40ulyssedaessle-e1634571514258-120x103.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110703/met-helmets-estro-mipsMET-Estro-Mips_P5102654_%40ulyssedaessle-e1634571514258-768x660.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110703/met-helmets-estro-mipsMET-Estro-Mips_P5102654_%40ulyssedaessle-e1634571514258.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-273836\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The MET Estro MIPS is a road-specific helmet with 26 vents, a dedicated sunglasses port, and a comfort-driven fit – all at a decent price (for high-end, feature-packed helmets).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1.jpg\" alt=\"a red MET estro mips helmet against a white background\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06174702/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347.jpg\" alt=\"MET Estro MIPS road helmet\" width=\"2291\" height=\"1388\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347.jpg 2291w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347-297x180.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347-800x485.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347-120x73.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347-768x465.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347-1536x931.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18111807/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139GI1-back-scaled-e1634570307347-2048x1241.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2291px) 100vw, 2291px\"></a></p><p>With ventilation a priority in the design, 17 of the Estro MIPS’ 26 vents are inlets and nine are exhaust holes. The helmet features MET’s Safe-T Upsilon retention system for a comfortable and versatile fit on, as MET says, “almost all different shaped heads, round or more oval.” Adding to the comfort is the 360° head belt with vertical adjustments, an adjustable divider, and hand-washable comfort pads.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139.jpg\" alt=\"MET Estro MIPS road helmet\" width=\"2361\" height=\"2009\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139.jpg 2361w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139-297x253.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139-800x681.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139-120x102.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139-768x653.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139-1536x1307.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110649/met-estro-mips-road-cycling-helmet-M139BI1-top-scaled-e1634570337139-2048x1743.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2361px) 100vw, 2361px\"></a></p><p>The full polycarbonate wrap and in-molded EPS liner work in conjunction with the <a href=\"https://mipsprotection.com/helmet-safety\">MIPS</a>-C2 <a href=\"https://mipsprotection.com/science-technology/mips-safety-system-functionality\">brain protection system</a>—a technology designed to reduce the rotational impact of a crash. As a refresher, the system claims to improve rider safety by allowing the helmet to move slightly in relation to the head in a crash, reducing the rotational forces applied to the brain.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors.jpg\" alt=\"MET Estro MIPS road helmet\" width=\"2343\" height=\"1224\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors.jpg 2343w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors-297x155.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors-800x418.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors-120x63.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors-768x401.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors-1536x802.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18110639/MED-Estro-MIPS-colors-2048x1070.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2343px) 100vw, 2343px\"></a></p><p>The MET Estro MIPS is aimed squarely at road, cyclocross, and gravel riders, and comes in small, medium, and large. A medium weighs in at 270g (9.5 ounces). The Estro MIPS will be available for purchase in November 2021 and is available in six colors at $159.</p><p><strong>MRSP:</strong><br><strong>• MET Estro Mips: </strong>130€ | £120 | US$159 | CAD$199 | AUS$199</p><p><strong>SPECS:</strong><br><strong>• Weight M size: </strong>270g<br><strong>• Sizes:</strong> S (52-56cm) | M (56-58cm) | L (58-61cm)<br><strong>• Certifications:</strong> CE; AS/NZS; US</p><p><strong>FEATURES:</strong><br><strong>• </strong>MIPS-C2® Brain Protection System, fully polycarbonate wrapped EPS liner to enhance durability, extended Head Coverage for deeper head protection, MET Safe-T Upsilon Fit System, 360° Head belt, vertical adjustment to maximize adjustability</p><p><a href=\"https://www.met-helmets.com/en/shop/cycling-helmets/road-helmets/estro-mips/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>met-helmets.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Andrew Marshall","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b3740f1253b50897f6fb0bb1056d2e538aacc796c159a98dc8819eb0dc7e672d","category":"Cycling"}